@Polymathj: That's because Comcast has a cap and actively works to analyze the traffic running over their network from high downloaders. Comcast sucks. Read up on their history with torrent traffic and you will know I speak the truth.

I recently moved from Comcast to FIOS. What a difference. No cap, no BS, and 5 MB/s downloads. Yes, Mega BYTES, not bits.

Peerblock is great though. I run that all the time. For downloading movies, though, I signed up for ipredator VPN service. Downloads are slower, but it gives you piece of mind since all traffic running over the VPN is encrypted. I use it whenever I download movies. Especially big name movies that are more likely to get tagged by ISPs or movie studios (such as this one).
